What is kanban?
Kanban principles
managing the flow and visualizing the work flow

What is kanban 
  •	Kanban is a continuous delivery system with no sprints
  •	Key principles
    o	Work in progress (WIP) limit
    o	Visualize work
    o	Manage work
    o	Improve continuously
  •	Managing Flow
    o	Work is pulled, not assigned
    o	Focus on finishing work before starting new items
    o	Measure cycle time and throughput
  •	Visualize work with limits
    o	WIP limit
    o	It restricts number of work items in a column
    o	Prevents overloading and multitasking
    o	Example if WIP limit = 3
    o	Then team should not begin new task 4 until one is finished



